dc_title_s: [Geological Survey of England and Wales : one inch to the mile map. New Series.] Wolverhampton, drift, sheet 153
dc_description_s: Geological Survey of Great Britain. Great Britain. Geological Survey of England and Wales. Sheet 153 drift. Great Britain. Ordnance Survey of England. North Decimal Degree 52.750000. South Decimal Degree 52.5833. East Decimal Degree -2.0667. West Decimal Degree -2.4833. In upper left margin: Ordnance Survey of England. Relief shown by contour interval and spot heights.Transverse Mercator projection. National grid system. "Original geological survey (on the one-inch scale) published and revised on Old Series maps 61 N.E. & S.E., 62 N.W. & S.W. in 1852-68. Re-surveyed (on the six-inch scale) in 1914-23 by T. C. Cantrill, et al.".
